<abstract>
<t>The Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP) specificationallows for the protection of network management operations by a variety of security protocols.  The SNMP administrative model described inprovides a framework for securing SNMP network management. In the context of that framework, this memo defines protocols to support the following three security services:</t>
<t>o data integrity,</t>
<t>o data origin authentication, and</t>
<t>o data confidentiality.</t>
<t>Please send comments to the SNMP Security Developers mailing list (snmp-sec-dev@tis.com).</t></abstract></front>

